{"Success":true,"Message":"Success","TotalRecord":1,"IsAuthFailure":false,"Data":[{"Tender_Id":99497100,"Bid_End_Date_Time":"05:05:2026 13:00","Bid_Opening_Date_Time":"Technical Bid Opening: 06:05:2026 11:00<br>Price Schedule Opening: Will be intimated to qualifying tenders after decision on qualifying bids","Department_Name":"RAJASTHAN RAJYA VIDYUT UTPADAN NIGAM LIMITED","Emd_Instrument_Type":"No","Completion_Period":"one year","Category":"Annual contract","Delivery_district":"Chhabra, Distt. Baran","Location":"CTPP Ash Dyke, Chhabra, Distt. Baran- 325220, Rajasthan","Products":"Lifting and transportation of Dry Fly Ash from 7x500MT RCC main silo/Intermediate silo (In case of emergency) of Unit#1 to 4, Lifting and transportation of Bottom Ash from IM silo of Unit # 1to4 and transportation of the same to CTPP Ash Dyke or designated place & spreading of Bottom Ash in Ash Dyke of CTPP, Chhabra","State":"Rajasthan","Estimated_Cost":"Rs.1,13,75,775/-","EMD_Value":"Rs.2,27,550/-","Document_Fees":"Rs. 5900/<br>(Rs.5000+GST@18%)","Work_to_be_Done_Site_or_Workshop":"Site","Payment_terms":"<p>100% payment after making necessary deduction (towards S.D., Taxes & others if any) shall be made by the Accounts Officer /AAO, CTPP, RVUNL, Chhabra against satisfactory performances of work done on monthly basis.</p>","Hard_Copy_Submission":"<p>Yes:<br/>Tender Application Form (To be sent via E-mail to aoctpp@rrvun.com and se1.camtc.ctpp@rrvun.com/in person/by post before schedule time of deposition of tender cost, tender processing fee and Bid Security)</p>","Levy_of_Penalty":"<p>24.01 In case the contractors does not supply the required T&P and/ or consumables, to complete the job, a deduction at the rate of Rs. 1000/- per day shall be made for the period in which contractor becomes defaulter & the same shall be arranged from the market on the risk and cost of the contractor in addition to penalty.<br/>24.02 In case contractor does not provide supervisor to meet the requirement of the contract work site a deduction at the rate of Rs. 500/- per day.<br/>24.03 In case of breakdown/shutdown/emergency maintenance work for which the contractor fails to do any work or part thereof due to his negligence within the prescribed time period given by the Engineer In charge, CTPP will be at liberty to recover from the contractor @ ½ % per hour after 25% of stipulated time subject to a maximum of 10% value of the particular work as per G-Schedule.<br/>24.04 In case of maintenance work to be done daily and found incomplete during checking due to one or other reasons, the recovery shall be imposed@100% of value of item work mentioned in G-Schedule.<br/>24.05 In case the contractor does not supply adequate manpower, penalty equal to the rate awarded in the work order for that manpower shall be deducted from the running bill. (i.e. deduction shall be-amount against shortfall of manpower + penalty @manpower rate awarded in contract).<br/>19.16 On failure of the contractor in complying with any of the above directions, the RVUN may at its discretion either cancel the contract or impose such penalty as deemed fit, which may be recovered from the security deposit or other claims payable to the contractor against this contract or any other payment due to him and/ or may take legal recourse for such recovery.</p>","Courier_Speed_Post_Submission":"<p>Tender Application Form should be sent via E-mail to aoctpp@rrvun.com and se1.camtc.ctpp@rrvun.com/in person/by post before the schedule time of deposition of tender cost, tender processing fee and Bid Security.</p>","Affidavit_notarized_documents":"<ul><li>Bidder should submit self attested declaration along with bid that firm is not debarred / blacklisted by any organization anywhere in india.</li><li>Self attested copy of all required documents.</li><li>The tenderer shall submit online all required documents digitally signed as prescribed in the qualifying requirement including self-attested/digitally signed copies of work/supply orders, performance certificate, solvency certificate of required value, registration certificates of Provident Fund and GST as applicable.</li></ul>","Eligibility_Criteria":"Here is the detailed Eligibility Criteria / Pre-Qualification Criteria (PQ/PQR) / Qualification of the Bidder based on the provided tender documents:<code><table>  <tr>    <th colspan=\"2\"><b>Qualifying Requirements (Q.R.)</b></th>  </tr>  <tr>    <td colspan=\"2\"><b>General Experience</b></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>Experience</td>    <td>      <ul>        <li>The bidder should have experience of either completed/under execution of the annual contract for loading &amp; transportation of fly ash / bottom ash or handling of fine /coarse aggregate of any material like ash/coal/sand/stone pebbles etc. in any State/Central/Semi Government department/process Industry/Industrial organization/reputed private industries during last 7 years ending last day of the month previous to the date of issue of the NIT.</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>Similar Work Experience</td>    <td>      <ul>        <li>One completed/under execution annual contract of above work, costing not less than the amount equal to 80% (Amounting to Rs. 91.00 Lakhs /-) of the estimated cost excluding taxes.</li>        <li>Two completed/under execution annual contracts of above work, costing not less than the amount equal to 50% (Amounting to Rs. 56.88 Lakhs/-) of the estimated cost excluding taxes each.</li>        <li>Three completed/under execution annual contracts of above work, costing not less than the amount equal to 40% (Amounting to Rs.45.50 Lakhs/-) of the estimated cost excluding taxes each.</li>        <li>Satisfactory performance certificate or satisfactory work completion certificate for above executed works should be signed by order placing authority/Order executing authority/Owner of the organization/ any authorized person and in case of works awarded by RVUN, performance certificate should be signed by Chief Engineer/In-charge of Power Station/Project.</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td colspan=\"2\"><b>Financial Standing</b></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>Average Annual Turnover</td>    <td>      <ul>        <li>Average Annual Financial Turn Over in the preceding three completed financial years (i.e. 2022-23, 2023-24 and 2024-25) as on date of issue of NIT should not be less than 30% of estimated cost (Amounting to Rs. 34.13 Lakhs).</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td colspan=\"2\"><b>Mandatory Registrations</b></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>Registrations</td>    <td>      <ul>        <li>The participating bidders should have PF Registration and ESI registration. Labour license of Baran district will be provided along with bid (if required).</li>        <li>The participating bidder/firm should have active GST Registration number and Permanent account Number (PAN).</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td colspan=\"2\"><b>Declarations</b></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>Declaration</td>    <td>      <ul>        <li>Bidder should submit self attested declaration along with bid that firm is not debarred / blacklisted by any organization anywhere in india.</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>   <tr>    <td >Performance of running contract</td>    <td >      <ul>       <li> If participating bidder having similar running contract at CTPP then he should submit satisfactory performance of running contract up to the month previous to the date of publication of the NIT along with bid.</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td >Documentary evidence</td>    <td >      <ul>       <li>Bidder shall furnish documentary evidence, copies of work order(s) along with satisfactory performance.</li>        <li>For completed work - Work order value will be considered.</li>        <li>For work under execution- The bidder should have achieved the progressive value specified in the Q. R. Sr. No. 1. The same shall be supported by documentary evidence issued as per Q. R. Sr. No. 2 above.</li>        <li>The biennial contract shall be treated/considered equivalent to two annual contracts of 50% contract value each.</li>        <li>The above orders should be directly placed on the bidder. Experience of sub-let work will not be considered.</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>   <tr>    <td >Financial documents</td>    <td >      <ul>       <li>Bidder shall furnish last three years (i.e. 2022-23, 2023-24 and 2024-25) audited balanced sheet duly attested by CA with his UDIN No. or Income Tax returns of same financial years may be taken from the bidder according to his turnover as per income tax laws. However RRVUN reserve the right to ask for furnishing audited trading account, certified copies of P&L account and balance sheet from any participating bidder.</li>        <li>Note: Other income shall not be considered for arriving at annual turnover.</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td >Code and licenses</td>    <td >      <ul>       <li>Provident fund code (PF Code) number allotted by concerned Regional Provident Fund Commissioner (RPFC).</li>        <li>Employees State Insurance Code (ESI Code) as having registered with ESI authorities.</li>        <li>Labour license of Baran District (if required). However, in Case the labour license is presently not available with the participating bidders/Firms, then they are required to furnish an undertaking dully attested by notary on NJSP of GoR of Rs. 100/-, that the required registration shall be obtained by them and furnished to RVUNL within one month of placement of LOI or commencement of work, whichever is earlier.</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>    <tr>    <td >GST and PAN</td>    <td >      <ul>       <li>Copy of GSTIN Registration (copy of latest GSTR return filled with GSTIN status as active) issued by concerned authorities and copy of Permanent account Number (PAN).</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td >Self attested declaration</td>    <td >      <ul>       <li>Self attested declaration along with bid that firm is not debarred / blacklisted by any organization.</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>    <tr>    <td >Satisfactory performance</td>    <td >      <ul>       <li>Bidder shall furnish documentary evidence of satisfactory performance issued from competent authority.</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td colspan=\"2\"><b>Additional Points</b></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>Validity of Tender</td>    <td>      <ul>        <li>The tender shall remain open for acceptance to the Nigam for a period of 180 days from the date and time on which techno commercial part of tenders are actually opened.</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>Earnest Money Deposit (EMD)</td>    <td>      <ul>        <li>The tenderer shall deposit an amount as indicated elsewhere as earnest money through digital mode (RTGS/NEFT) payable to the Assistant Accounts Officer (CTPP), RVUN, Chowki Motipura, Account no. 61005208761(IFSC Code-SBIN0031988 & MICR Code 325002019) well before scheduled date & time specified in tender document. Digital payment should be confirmed at Email-id aoctpp@rrvun.co.in&se1.camtc.ctpp@rrvun.com.</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>    <tr>    <td >Breach of Code of Integrity</td>    <td >      <ul>       <li>In case of breach of any provision of the code of integrity by a bidder or a prospective bidder, as the case may be, the procuring entity may take appropriate action in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (3) of Section-11 and Section-46 of the Rajasthan Transparency in Public Procurement Act'2012.</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr>      <tr>    <td >Qualification of Bidder</td>    <td >      <ul>       <li>Bidder should have to furnish declaration regarding qualification in Annexure-A \"Declaration by the bidder regarding qualification\" as per Section-7 of Rajasthan Transparency in Public Procurement Act, 2012.</li>      </ul>    </td>  </tr></table></code>","Checklist":"1. Scanned Copies of digital payment confirmation advice of tender cost2. Scanned Copies of digital payment confirmation advice of EMD3. Scanned Copies of digital payment confirmation advice of processing fee4. Documents related to qualifying requirement5. Details of technical specification6. Confirmation to commercial terms and conditions7. Details required in various Sections/ Schedules/ Annexure/ Forms except the Price Schedule/BOQ8. Authorization/Power of Attorney9. Tender Application Form10. Payment advice/ Unique Transaction Reference number (UTR No.)11. Self-attested/digitally signed copies of work/supply orders12. Performance certificate13. Solvency certificate of required value14. Registration certificates of Provident Fund15. GST registration16. Digital mode payment reference of EMD17. Digital mode payment reference of Tender cost18. Digital mode payment reference of processing fee19. Annexure A: Declaration by the bidder regarding Qualification20. Annexure B: Grievance Redressal during Procurement21. Bidders shall furnish documentary evidence, copies of work order(s)22. Satisfactory performance23. Audited balanced sheet duly attested by CA with his UDIN No. or Income Tax returns of same financial years24. Certified copies of P&L account25. Balance sheet from any participating bidder26. Provident fund code (PF Code) number allotted by concerned Regional Provident Fund Commissioner (RPFC)27. Employees State Insurance Code (ESI Code)28. Labour license of Baran District (if required)29. Undertaking dully attested by notary on NJSP of GoR of Rs. 100/-30. Copy of GSTIN Registration31. Permanent account Number (PAN)32. Self attested declaration33. Documentary evidence of satisfactory performance issued from competent authority34. Schedule A: Information about bidders35. Annexure C: Experience of work36. Annexure D: Experience of work37. Copies of executed work order38. Certificate of performance of work Issued by an officer not below the rank of Superintending Engineer / order placing authority (If available)39. Details of special T&P40. Solvency certificate41. Banker's Credit Certificate42. Documentary proof of status of the firm43. Schedule B: DEVIATION FROM SPECIFICATION44. Schedule C: DECLARATION OF BIDDER ABOUT APPLICABLE TAXES DETAILED IN THE PRICE SCHEDULE45. Income certificate of the firm for the last three years46. Copy of income tax return filed47. Copy of certificate if issued by Excise Department for non applicability of GST48. GST return filed central Excise Department49. Self Declaration Certificate50. Schedule D: REAL TIME GROSS SETTLEMENT (RTGS)/NATIONAL ELECTRONIC FUND TRANSFER51. Schedule E: INDENTURE FOR AGREEMENT52. FORM No.153. Annexure C: Details of Work Executed by the Bidder at CTPP During Last Five Years54. Annexure D: Details of Work Executed by the Bidder at Other Places/Plants (Excluding CTPP) During Last Five (5) Years"}],"StatusCode":200}